Source: ftnd
Section: comm
Priority: extra
Maintainer: Robert James Clay <jame@rocasa.us>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 9), dh-autoreconf, autotools-dev, libbz2-dev, libz-dev
Standards-Version: 3.9.3
Vcs-Git: git://github.com/jame/ftnd.git
Vcs-Browser: http://github.com/jame/ftnd
Homepage: http://jame.github.com/ftnd

Package: ftnd
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, adduser
Recommends: xinetd, arc, zip, unzip
Suggests: arj, unrar-free, zoo, lha, ha, joe, dosemu, dosemu-freedos, tetradraw
Description: FTNd Services for Unix
 FTNd is a full Fidonet capable mailer 
 package including a mailer, tosser, ticfile 
 processor, filefind and other utilities. 
 The mailer supports FTS-0001, YooHoo/2U2,
 EMSI protocols over modem, TCP/IP IFC and
 Binkp protocols. Zedzap, Zmodem, Telink and
 Hydra file transfer protocols.  Full FTN mail
 support, including automatic routing for hub
 and host systems.
 Internal mail format is JAM (c) messagebase.
 Full tic file support, including extended
 tic files.

Package: ftnd-dbg
Architecture: any
Section: debug
Depends: ftnd (= ${binary:Version}), ${misc:Depends}
Description: debugging symbols for ftnd
 MBSE BBS is a full Fidonet capable ANSI BBS package including a mailer,
 tosser, ticfile  processor, filefind and other utilities. The bbs supports
 full configurable ANSI  menus, multiple languages, standard file transfer
 protocols, native GNU/Linux doors, DOS doors using dosemu and BlueWave and
 QWK offline readers.
 .
 This package contains the debugging symbols for ftnd.
